inors; (e) there is no analogue\nof the odd-primary splitting of $(PL/O)_{(p)}$ for the prime 2; (f) for any\n$bP_{8j+4}$-sphere (where j > 0) of order which divides 4, the corresponding\nelement in $\\pi_0 Diff(D^{8j+2},\\partial)$ lifts to $\\pi_{8j-4}\nDiff(D^6,\\partial)$, i.e., lies correspondingly deep down in the Gromoll\nfiltration.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Dec 2016 14:26:27 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 14 Jun 2017 21:10:44 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 29 Aug 2018 12:04:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-11-22"}
